docs.abstract: Thomas J. Barrack Jr. attended two events with the president this week in California. Prosecutors have questioned him in their investigation of foreign influence in the 2016 campaign.
docs.snippet: Thomas J. Barrack Jr. attended two events with the president this week in California. Prosecutors have questioned him in their investigation of foreign influence in the 2016 campaign.
docs.lead_paragraph: When President Trump attended a fund-raiser at a private home in Beverly Hills on Tuesday night, there was a familiar face in the crowd: Thomas J. Barrack Jr., the billionaire investor and an old friend of the president’s who has come under scrutiny by federal prosecutors looking into possible foreign influence over Mr. Trump’s 2016 campaign.

headline.main: A Trump Friend, Under Scrutiny by Prosecutors, Appears at California Fund-Raisers

docs.abstract: A Bronx judge says the president must testify by videotape in a lawsuit brought by protesters who say his guards assaulted them.
docs.snippet: A Bronx judge says the president must testify by videotape in a lawsuit brought by protesters who say his guards assaulted them.
docs.lead_paragraph: A Bronx trial judge on Friday ordered President Trump to provide videotaped testimony for an upcoming trial over a lawsuit brought by protesters who say that his private security guards assaulted them on a public sidewalk in front of Trump Tower and stole a protest sign.

headline.main: President Must Tape Testimony for Trial Over 2015 Protest at Trump Tower

docs.abstract: The American military carried out an airstrike Thursday against Islamic State fighters in southern Libya in a reminder of the terrorist group’s resilience.
docs.snippet: The American military carried out an airstrike Thursday against Islamic State fighters in southern Libya in a reminder of the terrorist group’s resilience.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States military carried out an airstrike against Islamic State fighters in southern Libya on Thursday in a reminder of the terrorist group’s continuing operations and resilience far from its main guerrilla strongholds in Iraq and Syria.

headline.main: U.S. Drone Attacks ISIS Fighters in Southern Libya
headline.print_headline: U.S. Drone Strike in Libya Kills 8 at an ISIS Compound

docs.abstract: The funding cut was announced a week before Afghanistan holds national elections, and in the wake of failed peace talks with the Taliban.
docs.snippet: The funding cut was announced a week before Afghanistan holds national elections, and in the wake of failed peace talks with the Taliban.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The State Department cut $100 million in aid for Afghanistan on Thursday as the Trump administration’s chief peace negotiator briefed House lawmakers on the failed efforts to strike a deal with the Taliban and wind down the 18-year war.

headline.main: U.S. Cuts $100 Million in Aid to Afghanistan, Citing Government Corruption
headline.print_headline: Pompeo Cites  Corruption  As U.S. Cuts Afghan Aid

docs.abstract: China has experienced its “worst year” in 57 years, the president said Wednesday, a few years short of the 61 years he estimated last week and a couple of decades more than the 35 years he claimed last month.
docs.snippet: China has experienced its “worst year” in 57 years, the president said Wednesday, a few years short of the 61 years he estimated last week and a couple of decades more than the 35 years he claimed last month.
docs.lead_paragraph: First, the tariffs placed on Chinese imports have raised $27 billion, as of Aug. 28, and a number of recent studies have shown that the costs are borne by American companies and consumers, not by China. Analysts have estimated that the trade war would cost the average American family about $460 over a year.

headline.main: Fact-Checking Trump’s Claims About China’s ‘Worst Year’

docs.abstract: The question of whether Secretary of State Mike Pompeo will run for Senate in Kansas “hangs over the race a little bit,” said the leading Republican candidate.

docs.abstract: Mr. Gowdy, a former prosecutor who served four terms in the House before resigning in January, is expected to be a presence on television defending the president.
docs.snippet: Mr. Gowdy, a former prosecutor who served four terms in the House before resigning in January, is expected to be a presence on television defending the president.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Trey Gowdy, the former South Carolina congressman who led the committee that investigated the terrorist attack on the American diplomatic compound in Benghazi, Libya, that killed four Americans, will join President Trump’s legal team as an outside adviser.

headline.main: Trey Gowdy, Who Led Republicans in Investigating Benghazi, Joins Trump Legal Team
headline.print_headline: Gowdy Joins Legal Team For President As an Adviser

docs.abstract: The former U.S. ambassador to Ukraine gave an extraordinary interview to impeachment investigators.
docs.snippet: The former U.S. ambassador to Ukraine gave an extraordinary interview to impeachment investigators.
docs.lead_paragraph: Ms. Yovanovitch delivered her searing account before Congress at the risk of losing her job, since the White House has ordered officials not to cooperate with the impeachment inquiry. docs.abstract: The ruling, by a three-judge panel, handed a victory to House Democrats whose efforts to obtain the documents have been stonewalled by the White House.
docs.snippet: The ruling, by a three-judge panel, handed a victory to House Democrats whose efforts to obtain the documents have been stonewalled by the White House.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s accounting firm must comply with a House committee’s demands for eight years of his financial records, a federal appeals court panel ruled on Friday in a major victory for House Democrats in their struggle against his vow to stonewall “all” of their oversight subpoenas.

headline.main: Congress Can Seek Trump’s Financial Records, Appeals Court Rules
headline.print_headline: Congress Can Seek Trump’s Financial Records, Appeals Court Panel Rules

docs.abstract: Democrats in Congress have made a calculated decision not to call for a ban to be included in an emerging package of gun control measures.
docs.snippet: Democrats in Congress have made a calculated decision not to call for a ban to be included in an emerging package of gun control measures.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As Democrats make an aggressive push for new gun control legislation, they have made a calculated decision to stop short of pursuing their most ambitious goal: an assault weapons ban.

headline.main: Divided Democrats Step Back From Assault Weapons Ban
headline.print_headline: Support Erodes for a Ban on Assault Weapons
